Washington
Last updated at 12:37AM, September 28 2013
President Obama last night told his Republican foes on Capitol Hill to “knock it off” and do their duty as America stands on the brink of a catastrophic government shutdown.
Calling the Republicans in the House “extremists”, he urged them to pass a budget before the end of the financial year on Monday and stop putting American recovery and the world economy at risk.
There was a glimmer of good news as the Senate, with Republican support, passed a budget plan, stripping out a caveat that would have defunded the President’s flagship healthcare reforms.
